            "max_check_attempts": 5,
            "notes": "Monitors network interface errors per interface and alerts on receive and transmit errors. On Linux it additionally shows the receive and transmit error breakdown (the FIFO, frame and carrier error groups); on Windows only the receive and transmit error totals are available. Each counter is reported as a per-second rate measured between two check runs, so the values reflect the current situation rather than totals accumulated since boot. Alerts when the combined error rate (receive plus transmit errors) of an interface leaves the warning or critical range (default: warns on any new errors).",
